---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import ScrollReveal from "../components/ScrollReveal.tsx";
import { SITE } from "../config/site.mjs";
---

<Layout
  title={`About | ${SITE.title}`}
  description="Learn about Giveth House — a community-driven Web3 hub in Barcelona (Sants) supporting builders through coworking, events, and collaboration."
  canonicalURL={`${SITE.url}/about`}
>
  <Header />
  <main id="main-content" role="main">
    <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-20">
      <ScrollReveal client:idle>
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Giveth House</h1>
      </ScrollReveal>
      <ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.1}>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-12">
          Giveth House is a shared home, coworking space, and community hub in
          Barcelona&apos;s Sants neighborhood — a place where Web3 builders and
          communities meet, live, and collaborate in person.
        </p>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
          <h2>What is Giveth House</h2>
          <p>
            Giveth House is a physical gathering place for builders, researchers,
            organizers, and contributors working across the Web3 ecosystem. It
            offers a warm, community-oriented environment where people can stay,
            cowork, and host activities together.
          </p>
          <p>
            On any given week, the house might host people who are here to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              live temporarily while visiting Barcelona
            </li>
            <li>
              cowork with other builders and teams
            </li>
            <li>
              host workshops, talks, or small meetups
            </li>
            <li>
              collaborate on open-source and public goods projects
            </li>
            <li>
              gather informally to share ideas and experiences
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            More than just accommodation, the house acts as a{" "}
            <strong>Schelling point for the Web3 ecosystem</strong> — a place
            where collaborations and friendships naturally emerge.
          </p>
        </ScrollReveal>

        <ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.4}>
          <h2>Our Story</h2>
          <p>
            Giveth House was created in <strong>2017</strong>, shortly after
            the founding of the Giveth project in 2016. From the beginning, the
            team believed that even decentralized communities still benefit
            deeply from <strong>physical spaces</strong> where people can meet,
            collaborate, and build trust in real life.
          </p>
          <p>
            The house was set up to support contributors to Giveth, builders
            visiting Barcelona, members of the Ethereum ecosystem, and Web3
            communities organizing events and collaborations. Since then, it has
            welcomed <strong>hundreds of contributors</strong> from across the
            ecosystem.
          </p>
        </ScrollReveal>

        <ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.5}>
          <h2>Community &amp; Ecosystem</h2>
          <p>
            Over the years, Giveth House has become a small but important node
            in the broader Web3 landscape. Builders and contributors connected
            to projects such as:
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              Ethereum Foundation
            </li>
            <li>
              Arbitrum
            </li>
            <li>
              Starknet
            </li>
            <li>
              dOrg, Dappnode, Fuel Labs, Talent Layer, Blobscan, Vocdoni,
              General Magic, and others
            </li>
          </ol>
          <p>
            The house regularly hosts coworking sessions, hacker houses,
            community dinners, workshops, meetups, and collaborations between
            teams. The aim is simple: create an environment where{" "}
            <strong>serendipitous encounters lead to meaningful collaboration</strong>.
          </p>
        </ScrollReveal>

        <ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.5}>
          <h2>Values</h2>
          <p>
            Giveth House is inspired by the values that shaped the early
            Ethereum and Web3 communities. The space tries to embody:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              openness and transparency
            </li>
            <li>
              cooperation over competition
            </li>
            <li>
              decentralization and community governance
            </li>
            <li>
              freedom of thought and experimentation
            </li>
            <li>
              regenerative, positive-sum collaboration
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Many guests describe the house as having a{" "}
            <strong>solar-punk</strong> energy — optimistic, collaborative, and
            oriented toward building better systems together.
          </p>
        </ScrollReveal>

        <ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.6}>
          <h2>Stewardship &amp; Support</h2>
          <p>
            Since 2022, the house has been stewarded by{" "}
            <strong>Franco Ruiz</strong>, who coordinates guest stays, maintains
            the space, organizes activities, and supports collaborations between
            residents and visitors.
          </p>
          <p>
            Giveth House is sustained through{" "}
            <strong>community support and donations</strong> on the Giveth
            platform. Contributions help cover rent, utilities, maintenance, and
            operational costs so the house can continue to exist as a shared
            resource for the ecosystem.
          </p>
          <p>
            The long-term vision is for Giveth House to remain:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>a home for visiting contributors</li>
            <li>a meeting point for Web3 communities</li>
            <li>a place for experimentation and collaboration</li>
            <li>a welcoming entry point for new builders</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Ultimately, the house exists to strengthen the{" "}
            <strong>human connections</strong> that power decentralized
            networks.
          </p>
        </ScrollReveal>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
